                  </persName>
            . I am the wife of a coachman in Grafton Mews. I delivered a copper plate to Mr. Foy that I found in a basket over the coach-house; there was nothing else in the basket. The plate that I found there I threw behind the fire; when I took it out I knocked it with the poker; I threw it under the grate when I had knocked a piece off, and then I took it down and put it under the sill of the coach-house; it remained there until I gave it to Mr. Foy.</p>
               <p>Q. Had you any occasion to go into that room over the stable - A. Yes, I had occasion to go into it to get some things; it was locked.</p>
               <p>Q. Is that plate, No. 1, the same that you found in the basket - A. It appears like it. The one that I found in the basket I gave to Mr. Foy the next day, on the Wednesday. I also found some notes, I threw them in the fire.</p>
               <p>Q. You do not usually throw good notes in the fire - A. No; I found them in the clothes-pegs bag.</p>
